dct_title_s: Soil map, Indiana, Wells County sheet
dct_description_sm: Relief shown by contours. Shows distribution of soil types by colors and symbols. In lower margin: Engraved and published by the U.S. Geological Survey. U.S. Dept. of Agriculture, Bureau of Soils [and] State of Indiana, Department of Geology , soils surveyed by W.E. Tharp of the U.S. Department of Agriculture, in charge, and W.E. Wiley, of the Indiana Department of Geology.
Scale: 1:63,360. 1 inch = 1 mile; Dimensions: 64 x 53 cm
dct_creator_sm: Indiana. Department of Geology and Natural Resources; United States. Bureau of Soils; Wiley, W. E. (William Emmett), 1894-1967; Tharp, W. E. (William Edgar)
